# Navigation on command line

Ctrl-a : go to beginning of line
Ctrl-e : go to end of line
Ctrl-f : go forward one char
Ctrl-b : go back one char
Ctrl-k : kill (delete) the rest of line
Ctrl-y : yank (paste) the last killed line

# Search command line history
Ctrl-r cmd : Seaches the command history for 'cmd'
             multiple Ctrl-r will go cycle through history

# For a tutorial on navigating using these emacs shortcuts...
emacs
Ctrl-h t
